  <div class="section__body">
    <header role="title" class="body__header">
      <h5 class="body__header__title">HTML Guidelines</h5>
      <p>This table gives you a quick overview of the CSS classes that can be applied to create a table.</p>
    </header>
    <table class="table table-alpha">
      <thead>
        <th>Class Name</th>
        <th>Usage</th>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td style="width:30%">.table</td>
          <td>Set this class on the table element. This class applies the base styles that all tables inherit. <% code("html") do %><table class="table"><!-- Table Content --></table><% end %></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td style="width:30%">.table-alpha</td>
          <td>Set this class on the table element. This is the standard table class and should accompany the table class attribute. <% code("html") do %><table class="table table-alpha"><!-- Table Content --></table><% end %></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td style="width:30%">.table-bravo</td>
          <td>Set this class on the table element. This class should only be used for tables within tables. It has a slightly darker features.<% code("html") do %><table class="table table-bravo"><!-- Table Content --></table><% end %></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td style="width:30%">.table__row</td>
          <td>Set this class on the table row element of the parent table.<% code("html") do %><tr class="table__row"><!-- Table Content --></tr><% end %></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td style="width:30%">.table__hidden</td>
          <td>Set this class on the table row element that contains the nested table.<% code("html") do %><tr class="table__hidden"><!-- Table Content --></tr><% end %></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td style="width:30%">[aria-hidden="true"]</td>
          <td>Set this attribute on the table row element that contains the nested table.<% code("html") do %><tr class="table__hidden" aria-hidden="true"><!-- Table Content --></tr><% end %></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td style="width:30%">[aria-hidden="false"]</td>
          <td>Set this attribute on the table row element that contains the nested table when it is expanded.<% code("html") do %><tr class="table__hidden" aria-hidden="false"><!-- Table Content --></tr><% end %></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td style="width:30%">.table__header__icon</td>
          <td>Set this attribute on the table header element that contains an icon. For example a sort trigger. <% code("html") do %><th>Table Header <i class="table__header__icon"><%= image_tag 'icons/functional/sort-icon.svg' %></i></th><% end %></td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
